to the editor re a new doctrine for war news analysis front page march 18 it is important to recall that in the case of a war with iraq president bush 's policy is not one of pre emption but presumption he and his cabinet have presumed that iraq will carry out an attack against america in the future to go to war in the name of a presumption is tantamount to shooting first and asking questions later it makes for great theatrics but seldom results in stabilizing the world duncan b macdonald alexandria va march 18 2003

